---
import LegalPage from "../components/LegalPage.astro";
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Refund Policy - VivyShot"
  description="Refund guidance for official VivyShot purchases through Apple's App Store."
  canonicalPath="/refund"
  ogType="article"
>
  <LegalPage title="Refund Policy" lastUpdated="April 5, 2026">
    <section>
      <h2>Refunds for App Store Purchases</h2>
      <p>
        If official VivyShot binaries are sold through Apple’s App Store, Apple handles billing and
        refunds, and eligibility is determined by Apple’s policies.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>How to Request a Refund</h2>
      <p>To request a refund, use Apple’s official process:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Go to <a href="https://reportaproblem.apple.com">reportaproblem.apple.com</a></li>
        <li>Sign in with your Apple ID</li>
        <li>Find your VivyShot purchase</li>
        <li>Select "Request a refund" and follow the prompts</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Current Product Status</h2>
      <p>
        VivyShot is currently priced as a free base app, a $9.99 one-time Lifetime unlock, and an
        optional $24.99 Supporter purchase.
      </p>
    </section>
  </LegalPage>
</BaseLayout>
